During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Karine Jean-Pierre discussed various topics, including President Biden's upcoming trip to Allentown, Pennsylvania, the small-business boom under the Biden administration, and the new data on inflation and small-business applications. National Economic Advisor Lael Brainard also spoke about the President's trip to Allentown and the economic progress in the area. She highlighted the increase in jobs, access to high-speed internet, and investments in infrastructure and energy. Brainard also discussed the small-business boom across America and the reduction in inflation. She emphasized the importance of lowering costs for American households and called on corporations to pass along the savings to consumers.